Q2. Sprint Review in Agile

A Sprint Review is conducted at the end of a sprint to demonstrate completed work to stakeholders and collect feedback.

For example, if Zomato introduces a new Live Order Tracking feature, developers demonstrate the feature during the Sprint Review. Testers present testing results, including executed test cases, defects found, and defects fixed.

The testing team contributes by providing information about the quality and stability of the feature before release.


Q3. Agile Testing Activities During a Two-Week Sprint

Suppose WhatsApp is introducing a Dark Mode feature.

Activity 1

Requirement Review – Initially placed in the "To Do" column.

Activity 2

Test Case Preparation – Initially placed in the "To Do" column.

Activity 3

Functional Testing of Dark Mode – Initially placed in the "Backlog" column.

Activity 4

UI Testing on Different Devices – Initially placed in the "Backlog" column.

Activity 5

Regression Testing – Initially placed in the "Backlog" column.

These activities move across the Scrum Board as the sprint progresses.


Q4. Scrum Board Tasks for Instagram Stories Feature

I use Instagram daily, so I selected the Stories feature for this task.

Day 1 – Requirement Review and Test Case Preparation

The first step is to understand the Stories feature requirements and prepare test cases. This helps ensure that all expected functionalities are covered before testing begins.

Day 2 – Test Environment Setup

The testing environment and test accounts are prepared. This is necessary before executing any tests on the Stories feature.

Day 3 – Functional Testing

The tester verifies whether users can upload, view, delete, and share stories correctly. This ensures that the core functionality works as expected.

Day 4 – Defect Reporting and Retesting

Any defects found during functional testing are reported to developers. Once fixes are provided, the tester retests the feature to confirm that the issues are resolved.

Day 5 – UI Testing

The Stories interface, icons, buttons, and navigation are checked on different devices and screen sizes to ensure a good user experience.

Day 6 – Regression Testing

Regression testing is performed to ensure that the Stories feature has not affected other Instagram functionalities such as posts, reels, or direct messages.

Day 7 – Integration Testing and Final Verification

The Stories feature is tested with related modules such as user profiles, followers, and notifications. Final verification is performed before marking the feature as complete.

Conclusion

Breaking the Stories feature into multiple testing tasks helps the Scrum team track progress efficiently and ensures complete testing before release.